This paper deals with the geometric properties of drawings of graphs, specifically on the sphere or in the plane. This suggests that the paper may belong to the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the properties of the complete graph, which is a classic topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also involves the study of triangles and their properties, which is a topic in graph theory (cs.GT) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also involves counting and analyzing the number of empty triangles, which suggests that it may belong to the data structures (cs.DS) or social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-categories.
